article.description: Chris Ledlum scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds in his Harvard debut and the Crimson beat Division III-member MIT 84-27 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Ledlum's double-double sends Harvard past MIT 84-27
article.linkText: Ledlum's double-double sends Harvard past MIT 84-27
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Chris Ledlum scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds in his Harvard debut and the Crimson beat Division III-member MIT 84-27 on Tuesday night. Danilo Djuricic made a 3-pointer with 15:02 before halftime for a 13-4 Crimson lead. Harvard went on to a 33-10 halftime margin and then unloaded with a 51-point second half. Christian Juzang scored 12 points for Harvard, which saw 12 of 13 players that played enter the scoring column. Harvard's bench scored 41 points. The Crimson shot 34 of 60 (56.7%) from the field. Tim Kostolansky led MIT with eight points and seven rebounds.
